  "description": "Rule 90 — the Sierpinski triangle automaton. XOR of left and right neighbors draws a fractal. Seed 6553 produces an asymmetric starting colony. Medium scope (6) and moderate step rate (5 Hz) reveal the fractal structure through the filter modulation — cells 0–3 trace a self-similar pattern. filterRes at 0.52 adds mild resonance ringing on each fractal step. This is the engine's most geometrically pure state: the CA output IS the timbre, undisguised.",
